{%- assign sid = section.id -%}

{%- style -%}
#nx-what-{{ sid }} {
  max-width: var(--container-width-narrow);
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 8px 16px;
  font-family: var(--font-body-family, sans-serif);
  color: var(--color-text-main, #111827);
  line-height: 1.7;
  content-visibility: auto;
}
#nx-what-{{ sid }} h2 {
  font-family: var(--font-heading-family, sans-serif);
  font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px);
  font-weight: 700;
  line-height: 1.2;
  margin: 0 0 12px;
}
#nx-what-{{ sid }} p {
  color: var(--color-text-muted, #4b5563);
  max-width: 720px;
}
#nx-what-{{ sid }} p strong { color: var(--color-text-main, #111827); }
{%- endstyle -%}

<section id="nx-what-{{ sid }}" aria-label="What are racetams">
  <h2>What Are Racetams?</h2>
  <p>"Racetams" refers to a family of synthetic nootropics originating with Piracetam. On this page we focus on the <strong>in-stock</strong> options at Nootropix — <strong>Aniracetam, Fasoracetam, Phenylpiracetam Hydrazide</strong>, and <strong>Pramiracetam</strong> — plus their <strong>powder</strong> variants for flexible titration.</p>
</section>

